Three more syringes have been found hidden inside clothing at a Walmart store, raising the total to seven and prompting fears for customer safety.

A mother last week claimed her daughter was pierced by a syringe as she put on a new pair of pyjamas from the store in Georgia, Atlanta.

Now, in addition to three other incidents reported last month, two shoppers and a staff member have found needles in different pairs of trousers.

