She paid $1,300 for medicine to avoid an illness and took antiviral medicine. Walmart has now said it will cover her expenses.

A syringe was also found in a pair of Hello Kitty socks and a pair of trousers - but neither of those incidents resulted in any injuries.

A Walmart spokesman told the Rome News-Tribune that the company is looking at CCTV footage and employees are being extra vigilant.

